  "response_text": "# Healthy Lunar New Year Celebration Dinner\n\n## Main Dishes\n\n**Steamed Whole Fish with Ginger & Scallions**\n- Use fresh fish (symbolizes abundance)\n- Steam instead of frying\n- Season with fresh ginger, garlic, low-sodium soy sauce, and sesame oil\n- Garnish with cilantro and scallions\n\n**Chicken with Mushrooms & Chestnuts**\n- Poach or steam chicken breast\n- Use dried shiitake mushrooms (umami flavor without salt)\n- Add roasted chestnuts for traditional texture\n- Light broth base with herbs instead of salty sauces\n\n## Vegetables & Sides\n\n**Leafy Greens with Garlic**\n- Bok choy or gai lan (symbolizes prosperity)\n- Stir-fry with minimal oil and garlic\n- Use low-sodium soy sauce sparingly\n\n**Longevity Noodles**\n- Whole wheat or vegetable noodles\n- Toss with sesame oil, fresh herbs, and vegetables\n- Skip added salt; let diners season to taste\n\n## Dessert\n\n**Homemade Tangyuan (Sweet Rice Balls)**\n- Glutinous rice flour dough with sweet filling\n- Serve in light ginger or rock sugar syrup\n- No added sodium\n\n## Tips\n- Use fresh herbs and spices (ginger, star anise, Sichuan pepper) for flavor\n- Prepare broths from scratch to control sodium\n- Encourage family-style serving for portion awareness\n\nThis maintains symbolic traditions while supporting heart health!",
